WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.913
NARRATOR:
Previously on Smallville:

00:06.047 --> 00:08.379
CLARK: Isn't it time to move beyond
these mental trials?

00:08.550 --> 00:12.168
JOR—EL: When you decided to return to
your training, I assumed you were ready.

00:12.345 --> 00:14.802
-Tell me what you need.
JOR—EL: The test of a true hero...

00:14.973 --> 00:18.682
...is to struggle with feelings of loss,
not to avoid them.

00:18.852 --> 00:21.719
CLARK: I've come this far,
and I'm not looking back. I can do this.

00:22.605 --> 00:25.096
Pull an address
off of Queen lndustries' database.

00:25.275 --> 00:27.857
It's an engineer I ﬁred.
His name's Winslow Schott.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.609
CHLOE: What happened?
OLIVER: He snapped.

00:29.779 --> 00:33.067
He started bringing toys to work.
Then he started hiding explosives...

00:33.241 --> 00:34.447
...inside the toys.

00:34.617 --> 00:37.199
BOARD MEMBER: Oliver Queen,
what are you doing in enemy camp?

00:37.370 --> 00:40.578
OLIVER: I've purchased controlling interest
in LuthorCorp.

00:40.749 --> 00:42.535
Everybody down!

00:44.002 --> 00:47.586
-How does it feel to not be in control?
-Untie me right now.

00:47.756 --> 00:50.964
After this little fella
clangs his cymbals together 53 times...

00:51.134 --> 00:53.375
...it'll be the last sound you ever hear.

00:55.597 --> 00:58.259
CHLOE: Pieces of a toy bomb
were found in the wreckage.

00:58.433 --> 00:59.639
OLIVER:
Lex deserved to die.

00:59.809 --> 01:02.266
-This is murder.
-This is justice.

01:02.437 --> 01:05.474
Oliver crossed the line.
He killed Lex Luthor.

01:05.648 --> 01:07.559
You're making a big mistake.

01:07.734 --> 01:10.441
-What the hell were you so afraid of?
-You.

01:11.654 --> 01:14.896
-Maybe we should start over.
-lt's too late for that now.

01:15.408 --> 01:16.443
CLARK:
You need help.

01:16.618 --> 01:18.279
OLIVER: Not everybody believes in
the second coming.

01:18.453 --> 01:21.286
Is there any part of the person
I used to know still there?

01:21.456 --> 01:23.071
OLIVER:
You were right.

01:23.249 --> 01:25.410
I've been running away from myself
for a long time now.

01:25.585 --> 01:27.496
But now I know who I really am.

01:57.200 --> 01:59.191
[POLICE SIRENS WAILING]

02:05.458 --> 02:07.039
COP:
People, let's set up a perimeter.

02:07.210 --> 02:10.168
Get me a sightline. We don't know
how many hostages are inside.

02:10.338 --> 02:13.956
Get me a barricade. Last thing we need
is anyone getting in our way.

02:14.801 --> 02:16.166
Let's go. Let's move it.

02:44.581 --> 02:46.663
Don't bother pulling the trigger.

02:56.885 --> 02:58.250
[BEEPING]

03:04.017 --> 03:05.427
[SCREAMS]

03:13.610 --> 03:14.941
[SILENCE]

03:16.738 --> 03:19.024
[OVERLAPPING VOICES]

03:22.410 --> 03:24.401
[ALL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

03:46.601 --> 03:49.092
Clark. Did I miss him?

03:49.270 --> 03:53.183
-If by "him" you mean me, barely.
-Not you, the Blur.

03:53.358 --> 03:56.065
Oh, he was long gone
by the time I got here.

03:56.236 --> 03:57.817
I was just trying to call you.

03:57.987 --> 04:01.320
-From a payphone?
-Apparently.

04:01.491 --> 04:03.573
How'd you get here so fast, anyway?

04:03.743 --> 04:06.610
My guy at Met P.D. didn't leak this
until a few minutes ago.

04:06.788 --> 04:08.995
We all can't be as fashionably late
as Lois Lane.

04:09.165 --> 04:10.496
[LOIS CHUCKLES]

04:18.007 --> 04:21.591
LOIS:
Oh. Hello, sailor.

04:27.058 --> 04:29.720
-What'd you just say?
-Nothing.

04:29.894 --> 04:31.634
You should get your hearing checked.

04:31.813 --> 04:33.394
LOIS:
Hot stuff.

05:33.249 --> 05:35.740
LOIS: God, I am dragging ass today.
I should go for coffee.

05:35.918 --> 05:37.954
No, no.
What I actually need is a B12 shot.

05:38.129 --> 05:39.869
[have to keep up with Clark.

05:40.048 --> 05:42.460
Remember what the general says:
"On certain days...

05:42.633 --> 05:46.672
you wear certain underwear. "
And why you decided to go with a tho-

05:47.930 --> 05:48.965
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

05:49.140 --> 05:50.596
Hey, Smallville.

05:59.484 --> 06:00.599
You're in a good mood today.

06:00.777 --> 06:02.438
Would be in an even better one...

06:02.612 --> 06:05.945
...if our black-clad hero in hiding
would've stuck around for a quote.

06:06.115 --> 06:09.107
We'd at least know
what the hell happened back there.

06:10.411 --> 06:12.618
What happened
is the Blur saved those hostages.

06:12.789 --> 06:15.121
-End of story.
-There's always more to the story.

06:15.291 --> 06:18.499
The bomber isn't the one who ﬂipped
the switch. It was on a timer.

06:18.669 --> 06:21.126
Why would the bomb be on a timer?

06:21.631 --> 06:23.337
I don't know. I'm not a mind reader.

06:23.549 --> 06:26.040
Why would you take hostages
and not make any demands?

06:26.594 --> 06:30.462
LOIS: No voicemails. No e-mails.
Just be a big girl and get over the fact...

06:30.640 --> 06:35.134
...that the Blur downgraded you
from conﬁdante to sidekick to nobody.

06:35.311 --> 06:37.142
Lois.

06:38.189 --> 06:40.931
Computer‘s frozen again.

06:42.652 --> 06:44.188
LOIS:
Doesn't help that intern Jeff...

06:44.362 --> 06:47.980
...took the last stupid maple doughnut
from the stupid doughnut box.

06:50.993 --> 06:52.654
Here you go.

06:52.829 --> 06:55.696
My eyes are bigger
than my stomach this morning.

06:55.873 --> 06:58.159
No. Okay, I love you.

06:58.709 --> 07:01.837
Bump in blood sugar might help you
from punching someone.

07:02.004 --> 07:04.666
True. Give me that.

07:04.841 --> 07:06.172
Uh....

07:06.843 --> 07:10.381
Whoever did what he did, he couldn't
have picked a less interesting place.

07:10.596 --> 07:12.132
Run-of-the-mill textile factory?

07:12.306 --> 07:14.797
Factory which is a subsidiary
of Queen Industries.

07:14.976 --> 07:17.718
You think it'd be enough
to get Oliver's attention.

07:17.895 --> 07:21.183
LOIS: That only matters
if Ollie 's sober enough to give a crap.

07:21.357 --> 07:23.689
-You might be right.
-What'd you say?

07:25.027 --> 07:27.643
-What?
-What?

07:36.330 --> 07:37.365
Thanks for meeting me.

07:37.540 --> 07:40.532
-I know you've been busy.
-What am I thinking right now?

07:40.710 --> 07:43.201
No clue. So far, it's only been Lois.

07:43.379 --> 07:44.539
Okay.

07:44.714 --> 07:48.377
Well, I know that my Wall of Weird
is so three upgrades ago...

07:48.551 --> 07:51.167
...but I've spent enough time
digitizing the strange...

07:51.345 --> 07:55.930
...and unexplained in my life
to know that you don'tjust catch ESP.

07:56.142 --> 07:59.600
So how do we know that this isn't just
your super-hearing on the fritz?

07:59.770 --> 08:02.898
As loud as Lois is, even she can't speak
with her mouth closed.

08:04.192 --> 08:05.728
Good point.

08:05.902 --> 08:08.735
Okay, I'll see what I can dig up,
but seriously, Clark...

08:08.905 --> 08:13.148
...unless your warranty's expired,
just check in with dear old Dad.

08:13.910 --> 08:15.025
You okay?

08:16.162 --> 08:20.451
Yeah, I'd just like to bypass
Lois' inside voice from here on out.

08:20.666 --> 08:22.577
I'm ﬁne.

08:23.252 --> 08:25.163
I'll keep you posted.

08:31.260 --> 08:34.002
MAN: Can't miss this meeting,
or I'm gonna get ﬁred.

08:34.764 --> 08:36.254
WOMAN:
This isn't the life I wanted.

08:36.432 --> 08:38.263
MAN:
You should've told me that before.

08:38.434 --> 08:41.426
[OVERLAPPING VOICES
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

08:55.785 --> 08:57.491
Jor-El.

08:58.829 --> 09:01.115
Reading people's thoughts.

09:01.832 --> 09:04.414
You said my trials had begun.
Is this one of them?

09:04.585 --> 09:07.327
JOR-EL: lplanted within you
the seeds for this trial...

09:07.505 --> 09:11.339
...designed to self-manifest
when most needed.

09:11.509 --> 09:13.670
An event must've happened
to trigger it...

09:13.844 --> 09:16.301
...some kind of error
or mistake in judgment.

09:16.472 --> 09:18.463
I don't understand.

09:18.641 --> 09:20.802
I saved everyone in that factory.

09:20.977 --> 09:22.308
JOR-EL:
Assumptions are ﬂaws...

09:22.478 --> 09:25.015
...inherent in the human instincts
you have adopted...

09:25.231 --> 09:27.313
...but they are beneath you.

09:27.483 --> 09:31.442
What you have yet to nurture
is your Kryptonian intuition.

09:32.029 --> 09:36.193
-You shouldn't underestimate humans.
JOR-EL: Neither should you.

09:36.367 --> 09:39.951
Being able to discern
why humans truly behave as they do...

09:40.121 --> 09:42.988
...will help you to better protect them.

09:43.165 --> 09:48.205
This ability is only temporary.
You must learn to focus, Kai-El.

09:48.379 --> 09:53.043
Perception can be the difference
between life and death.

09:59.432 --> 10:00.888
LOIS:
I know loose lips sink ships...

10:01.058 --> 10:04.175
...but tight ones don't do
a hell of a lot of good either.

10:06.188 --> 10:08.019
Listen, Chatty Cathy,
we just need one answer.

10:08.190 --> 10:09.930
You were actually a hostage, right?

10:12.278 --> 10:14.860
This one's getting us nowhere.

10:15.031 --> 10:17.067
WOMAN [IN FOREIGN ACCENT]:
Do not let them ﬁnd out.

10:17.241 --> 10:18.651
They can't send me back.

10:19.201 --> 10:20.862
My baby needs me.

10:21.329 --> 10:23.911
It's okay, you can talk to us.

10:24.081 --> 10:25.457
We're not INS.

10:29.837 --> 10:33.455
I am sorry. I saw a man.

10:41.515 --> 10:44.382
So let me get this straight.
The guy who took you hostage...

10:44.560 --> 10:49.554
...was short and fat, but also tall?

10:49.940 --> 10:52.898
Yeah, way taller
than your boyfriend there.

10:53.361 --> 10:55.693
Um, thin.

10:55.863 --> 10:57.524
Thin like a rail.

10:57.698 --> 11:01.407
MAN: This is so exciting.
I wonder who will talk to me next.

11:02.036 --> 11:04.903
The FBI? Maybe Interpol.

11:05.414 --> 11:08.747
It's clear that this is the most
excitement you've had probably ever.

11:08.918 --> 11:12.160
You can mislead us, but interfering
with a police investigation...

11:12.338 --> 11:16.126
...to keep yourself in the limelight
will only land you in jail.

11:16.342 --> 11:17.582
Is that understood?

11:18.260 --> 11:19.591
Huh.

11:23.724 --> 11:25.260
Sorry.

11:26.602 --> 11:28.183
I didn't see anything.

11:34.610 --> 11:39.104
NURSE: I don't care how cute he is.
I better not get ﬁred for this.

11:39.865 --> 11:42.277
I haven't seen you eat a thing all day.

11:43.160 --> 11:46.277
Owed you from earlier.
Low blood sugar and all.

11:48.708 --> 11:52.542
Oh, look at this.
Thanks for taking care of me.

11:52.712 --> 11:54.122
Wait.

11:56.924 --> 11:58.084
Now we're even.

11:59.927 --> 12:01.883
What else did you ﬁnd out?

12:02.054 --> 12:04.966
Mr. Murphy, our mystery man's puppet,
just got out of surgery.

12:05.141 --> 12:08.804
-He's still unconscious.
-l've hit enough dead ends for today.

12:08.978 --> 12:11.640
Really no reason
for us to keep hanging out here, huh?

12:11.814 --> 12:13.896
You're absolutely right.

12:17.319 --> 12:19.230
Why don't we just call it a night?

12:19.989 --> 12:22.321
That's good. I have plans.

12:22.825 --> 12:24.736
LOIS:
Little Lifetime and some Chunky Monkey.

12:24.910 --> 12:26.992
Or Rocky Road. Maybe both.

12:27.163 --> 12:28.994
Lois.

12:31.834 --> 12:34.166
I was hoping we could
grab something to eat tonight...

12:34.336 --> 12:35.997
...once we ﬁnished up.

12:36.172 --> 12:39.289
You know, you said yourself
I hadn't eaten all day.

12:39.925 --> 12:42.792
LOIS:
ls Clark Kent asking me out on a date?

12:42.970 --> 12:44.005
Like a "date" date?

12:44.180 --> 12:46.842
-l'm not saying we should go on a date.
LOIS: Oh.

12:47.850 --> 12:50.592
Just something like a date.

12:51.020 --> 12:55.013
As sweet as that notion is, Smallville,
this is Metropolis on a Saturday night.

12:55.191 --> 12:57.898
We ain't getting in anywhere
without a reservation.

12:58.068 --> 13:00.400
LOIS:
Except maybe the truck rally downtown...

13:00.571 --> 13:01.731
...but there's no way he'd-

13:01.906 --> 13:04.488
We could probably get tickets
to the monster-truck rally.

13:04.658 --> 13:06.819
It doesn't start for a few more hours.

13:06.994 --> 13:08.359
LOIS:
Shut up.

13:09.872 --> 13:11.362
I'll meet you there.

13:11.540 --> 13:12.996
Standard protocol.

13:13.167 --> 13:17.035
Two cars at the beginning of the night,
no drama at the end of it.

13:17.880 --> 13:19.461
[CHUCKLES]

13:28.933 --> 13:30.924
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

13:44.907 --> 13:47.899
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

14:12.852 --> 14:15.093
You going our way?

14:16.105 --> 14:20.314
Barkeep, I'm gonna need,
um, something cold...

14:20.484 --> 14:23.351
...tall, wet, sexy. Put, uh....

14:23.529 --> 14:25.565
-Put one of these in it, will you, please?
-Tres.

14:26.782 --> 14:30.900
Looks like I got dollar bills.
I got pesos. I got, uh....

14:32.037 --> 14:35.621
Is that a euro? I don't--
I got this purple thing. These are fun. Um....

14:35.791 --> 14:36.826
[WOMEN LAUGH]

14:37.001 --> 14:39.083
Why don't we--?
Just take the whole thing...

14:39.253 --> 14:42.040
...and have a little vacation on me.
How does that sound? Okay?

14:42.214 --> 14:43.875
[DOOR BANGS OPENS]

14:50.306 --> 14:52.217
[IN SPANISH]

14:52.391 --> 14:55.554
[IN SPANISH]

14:56.562 --> 14:59.053
[IN ENGLISH]
What are you doing with my wife?

15:08.324 --> 15:09.814
[IN SPANISH]

15:11.827 --> 15:13.033
Hmm?

15:15.623 --> 15:16.658
[GRUNTS]

15:19.418 --> 15:20.749
[WOMEN SCREAMS]

15:23.923 --> 15:24.958
Really?

15:42.107 --> 15:45.691
You know, Mercy, if you wanted more
face time, all you had to do was ask.

15:52.952 --> 15:55.489
This is me asking.

16:11.345 --> 16:13.631
Whoa, Lois.

16:13.806 --> 16:16.343
-Why so fancy?
-Monster trucks.

16:16.809 --> 16:17.844
-Monster trucks?
-Mm-hm.

16:18.018 --> 16:19.804
Lois, I've seen you do
monster trucks before.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.810
This is deﬁnitely more than that.

16:21.981 --> 16:25.974
I would say that this is strictly
rhinestones-on-mud-ﬁaps territory.

16:26.151 --> 16:27.527
Who's the prince charming?

16:29.905 --> 16:32.863
I never thought
I'd say this out loud, but...

16:34.243 --> 16:35.528
...Clark Kent.

16:37.413 --> 16:40.826
I know. It's the weirdest thing.
Of the ﬁve things to do in Kansas...

16:41.000 --> 16:44.163
...Clark picked the one thing
I've wanted to do for weeks.

16:44.336 --> 16:47.248
We've been on the same wavelength
like all day today.

16:49.091 --> 16:52.879
I'll bet.
Sort of like he's been reading your mind?

16:53.053 --> 16:56.386
Like he's hearing things
that you've never actually said out loud?

16:56.557 --> 16:58.263
Exactly.

16:59.101 --> 17:01.262
Huh. That is the weirdest thing.

17:02.646 --> 17:05.558
Me and Clark. I don't know.

17:05.733 --> 17:08.190
I mean, we certainly kick
all kinds of ass at work...

17:08.360 --> 17:13.730
...but lately, it feels like we're more
than just partners, you know?

17:14.533 --> 17:17.525
I think I've gotten so used
to carrying the load all by myself.

17:17.703 --> 17:20.194
What if I don't have to anymore,
you know?

17:20.372 --> 17:23.034
Clark and Lois vs. the world.

17:24.001 --> 17:25.241
Oh, wow.

17:25.794 --> 17:27.910
Kind of lost myself
in there somewhere, huh?

17:29.131 --> 17:30.621
Don't wait up.

17:40.809 --> 17:44.973
MAN: He forced me to do it.
It wasn't me. I'm innocent.

17:45.147 --> 17:48.981
He strapped the bomb on me.
I just work there.

17:49.151 --> 17:53.645
He said toys weren't good enough.
He wants to play a game.

17:53.822 --> 17:57.314
He said Queen will pay
for what he's done to him.

17:59.787 --> 18:00.822
Toyman.

18:05.250 --> 18:07.241
[TOYMAN GIGGLING]

18:09.505 --> 18:10.836
TOYMAN:
Let the games begin.

18:11.006 --> 18:12.997
[TOYMAN GIGGLING MANIACALLY]

18:33.737 --> 18:34.772
[BEER BOTTLE OPENS]

18:34.947 --> 18:38.064
What the hell were you thinking, Oliver?

18:39.952 --> 18:42.944
-They could've killed you.
-Yeah.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.453
[GRUNTS]

18:44.915 --> 18:49.500
Didn't really give them a chance, did you?
And now we'll never know.

18:49.670 --> 18:52.707
Were you even aware
that one of your factories blew up?

18:54.258 --> 18:57.671
Do you give a damn
about anything anymore?

18:58.095 --> 19:02.088
Tell me you didn't waste all that jet fuel
to come here and deliver me a lecture.

19:02.266 --> 19:04.473
Your company's failing.

19:05.853 --> 19:09.061
Your stock is worth less
than you think of yourself right now.

19:10.482 --> 19:14.066
There's only so much more loss the
shareholders will be willing to accept.

19:14.570 --> 19:17.437
I'm tired of making excuses.

19:17.614 --> 19:19.650
Well, then why don't you stop
making excuses?

19:19.825 --> 19:21.986
Tell them the truth about me.

19:22.494 --> 19:23.904
Then you can become sole CEO.

19:24.079 --> 19:27.037
It'll be great for you.
It's what you always wanted, right?

19:31.003 --> 19:35.747
I've seen you go off the rails before,
but this...

19:37.593 --> 19:40.380
...this vanishing act, huh...

19:40.554 --> 19:42.419
...these binges...

19:43.432 --> 19:45.514
...you're punishing yourself.

19:46.852 --> 19:48.433
Why?

20:03.327 --> 20:05.693
Oliver, what did you do?

20:13.170 --> 20:18.130
No matter what this is about,
I understand.

20:19.426 --> 20:21.132
You know that.

20:27.601 --> 20:29.637
Just talk to me.

20:36.860 --> 20:40.773
You know, it sounds like you're the one
who needs to do the talking.

20:42.658 --> 20:46.822
So I guess the real question is,
what is it that you want from me?

20:55.337 --> 20:59.797
I need your pretty face
addressing our shareholders.

21:01.343 --> 21:03.959
Consider this one of the many favors
you owe me.

21:06.098 --> 21:07.759
[CHUCKLES]

21:15.857 --> 21:16.937
Is that all you want?

21:18.402 --> 21:21.940
I've learned not to expect too much
from you, Oliver.

21:23.323 --> 21:24.859
Cheer up.

21:25.033 --> 21:28.196
You can fall down drunk in a gutter
as soon as it's done.

21:32.374 --> 21:34.456
Wheels up in 20.

21:49.474 --> 21:52.090
CHLOE: It's a good thing he can't hear
what I'm thinking, or else-

21:52.269 --> 21:54.100
Or else what, Chloe?

21:56.481 --> 21:58.858
I would tell you
that I don't want you breaking...

21:59.026 --> 22:01.563
...my cousin's heart.
How was I supposed to react...

22:01.737 --> 22:04.900
...when I ﬁnd out that you've been
riﬁing through Lois' brain...

22:05.073 --> 22:08.782
...like you lost your keys in there?
You can't trick someone into dating you.

22:08.952 --> 22:11.034
I didn't trick her, and it's not a date.

22:11.204 --> 22:14.241
You didn't see her when she left.
Believe me, it was a date.

22:14.416 --> 22:17.658
And to add insult to injury,
now you're standing her up?

22:17.836 --> 22:19.747
No, I asked her out, not on a date...

22:19.921 --> 22:22.754
...before I knew our bomber
was an innocent man.

22:25.969 --> 22:28.460
-Toyman's back.
-Winslow Schott is responsible...

22:28.638 --> 22:32.176
...for the explosion at Oliver's building.
That's why I didn't call Lois back.

22:32.351 --> 22:36.310
The last thing I need is her showing up
here and following me into harm's way.

22:36.730 --> 22:39.563
Winslow's trying to smoke Oliver
out of hiding. He's insane.

22:39.733 --> 22:44.272
Yeah, he was crazy enough before Oliver
framed him for Lex's murder.

22:45.113 --> 22:49.106
If he's trying to track Oliver down,
he won't have a hard time doing it tonight.

22:50.160 --> 22:54.904
Oliver's addressing his shareholders
at your requisite red-carpet, black-tie gala.

22:57.459 --> 22:58.619
Head back to Watchtower.

22:58.794 --> 23:01.080
If Winslow strikes again,
we need to move fast.

23:14.351 --> 23:16.467
Mr. Pierson.

23:16.645 --> 23:18.260
Kirkpatrick.

23:18.438 --> 23:24.308
BOUNCER: Let's see. "Kendall. Kennair."
Ah, there it is. "Kirkpatrick. "

23:25.737 --> 23:28.228
Have a good evening, Mr. Kirkpatrick.

23:28.407 --> 23:31.149
-Name?
-Kennair.

23:31.993 --> 23:33.984
You have a plus-one tonight,
Mr. Kennair.

23:34.162 --> 23:35.823
[TIRES SQUEAL]

23:38.500 --> 23:40.411
[MONSTER TRUCK DOOR SHUTS
THEN LOIS GRUNTS]

23:43.880 --> 23:46.337
-Lois.
-I can handle this, Smallville.

23:46.508 --> 23:50.000
-You've already done enough tonight.
-What are you doing here?

23:50.178 --> 23:53.341
LOIS: Standing in the shadow
of 6-and-a-half feet of handsome.

23:53.890 --> 23:58.008
No, Lois, he doesn't get off that easy.
Kick his ass.

23:59.146 --> 24:03.856
Do you think not having a cocktail dress,
and being three steps behind you...

24:04.025 --> 24:07.153
...on your mystery-man story
was gonna stand in my way, did you?

24:07.320 --> 24:11.154
Or that you hid the fact that
Oliver returned for the sake of an article?

24:11.324 --> 24:16.444
Clark, you can't get rid of me that easily.
I have the Internet on my phone.

24:17.581 --> 24:19.196
-I can explain.
-Oh.

24:19.666 --> 24:21.202
I know how the boys' club works.

24:21.376 --> 24:23.867
You wanted to scoop me on a story.
Prose before ho's.

24:24.045 --> 24:26.081
-Now, wait a second.
BOUNCER: Good evening.

24:26.256 --> 24:29.464
LOIS: How could you be so stupid?
This was never about more than a story.

24:29.634 --> 24:31.795
Maybe it never will be.

24:33.597 --> 24:35.758
For your sake,
there better be an open bar...

24:35.932 --> 24:39.971
...because I think that Bone Dog
has my purse in his truck.

24:40.353 --> 24:41.684
[CHUCKLES]

24:50.322 --> 24:54.361
You know, Lois, I don't need your help
on this one. I can do it on my own.

24:54.826 --> 24:58.535
Maybe you'd like to think that you can,
but we all know there's no way.

24:59.998 --> 25:01.579
This is my headline.

25:01.750 --> 25:04.833
LOIS: Oh, God. Why would you
let yourself get attached, Lois?

25:05.003 --> 25:07.335
You know better than that.

25:07.923 --> 25:10.289
They always leave.

25:10.467 --> 25:12.583
You know what? Maybe you're right.

25:14.763 --> 25:17.755
I'm gonna get some air.
Some really private air.

25:17.933 --> 25:19.924
I'm out of here. Good luck ﬂying solo.

25:23.021 --> 25:24.852
Lois.

25:27.275 --> 25:28.776
MAN 1:
Maybe I should buy her a drink.

25:28.944 --> 25:31.356
WOMAN 1:
I can 't afford to lose any more money.

25:31.530 --> 25:33.395
MAN 2:
Look at this party, huh?

25:33.573 --> 25:35.359
WOMAN 2:
Mercer never should've. . ..

25:35.534 --> 25:38.241
WOMAN 3:
Oh, I hope this comes out in the wash.

25:38.411 --> 25:39.867
MAN 3:
Everyone said it was a gamble.

25:40.038 --> 25:41.619
WOMAN 4:
This was supposed to put....

25:41.790 --> 25:43.746
MAN 4:
She doesn't know this suit is a rental.

25:43.917 --> 25:45.782
MAN 5:
What the hell does she really want?

25:45.961 --> 25:47.622
MAN 6:
I can 't lose any more money.

25:47.796 --> 25:49.627
MAN 7:
If! leave, they'll follow me.

25:49.798 --> 25:52.380
WOMAN 5:
So the devil came in a blue dress tonight.

25:52.551 --> 25:53.882
Ladies and gentlemen...

25:55.470 --> 25:59.554
...your fearless leader, Oliver Queen.

26:00.350 --> 26:04.514
WOMAN 6: Look who decided
to grace us with his presence.

26:05.647 --> 26:07.763
Thank you. Ahem.

26:07.941 --> 26:08.976
Thank you, everyone.

26:09.150 --> 26:11.732
I know this has been a trying year
for all of you.

26:11.903 --> 26:16.317
And hopefully I can remain upright
long enough to say what...

26:16.491 --> 26:18.322
...needs to be said.

26:19.619 --> 26:23.111
Obviously, whoever wrote this speech
has a pretty good sense of humor.

26:23.290 --> 26:24.496
[INVESTORS LAUGH]

26:29.087 --> 26:31.078
Excuse me. It's my....

26:31.715 --> 26:36.254
Sorry. Technical difﬁculties here.
One moment.

26:36.428 --> 26:38.259
[LOUD RINGING]

26:50.692 --> 26:52.182
Thanks, Dad.

26:52.861 --> 26:54.476
TOYMAN [OVER RADIO]:
Oh, yes, Mr. Queen...

26:54.654 --> 26:57.361
...it's your old playmate Winslow Schott.

26:57.532 --> 26:59.568
I'm sure you remember.

26:59.743 --> 27:02.610
You framed me for murder, after all.

27:04.831 --> 27:08.323
And now that I've ﬁnally won
your little game of hide-and-seek...

27:08.501 --> 27:12.335
...I thought we might play something
that I'm a little more comfortable with.

27:12.505 --> 27:13.881
Toyman says...

27:14.424 --> 27:17.336
...read everything I've written,
or you will die.

27:17.510 --> 27:19.762
Toyman says...

27:19.929 --> 27:22.341
...don't try to run. Don 't take a step.

27:22.515 --> 27:26.007
If you move one muscle,
I will kill everybody in this room.

27:26.978 --> 27:28.479
[OVER RADIO]
Toyman says...

27:28.647 --> 27:31.514
...you're standing on a pressure plate.

27:32.317 --> 27:33.853
Toyman says...

27:34.486 --> 27:36.067
...you're standing on a bomb.

27:36.237 --> 27:37.568
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

27:47.582 --> 27:50.164
I've never truly worked
a day in my life.

27:50.877 --> 27:54.335
Too busy gagging on
the silver spoon...

27:55.590 --> 27:57.922
...wedged down my throat.

27:59.678 --> 28:03.170
And even when given
a second chance at life, I was, uh....

28:03.348 --> 28:06.181
I was unable
to see past my selﬁsh nature.

28:06.351 --> 28:08.057
TOYMAN [OVER RADIO]:
Oh, don't stop there.

28:08.228 --> 28:10.719
We haven't even gotten
to the good part yet.

28:16.736 --> 28:17.942
Time and again...

28:18.405 --> 28:22.023
...l've put my own needs over the needs
of my devoted employees.

28:22.617 --> 28:25.529
The only thing I've ever
been selﬂess enough to part with...

28:25.704 --> 28:27.786
...is the blame...

28:31.751 --> 28:32.957
...for a heinous act.

28:33.461 --> 28:35.452
No. Chloe, the trials aren't over.

28:35.630 --> 28:37.586
I just got my training wheels taken away.

28:37.757 --> 28:39.793
Jor-El wants me to use
what I've learned.

28:39.968 --> 28:42.084
[OVER PHONE]
Can you hack the feeds of the building?

28:42.262 --> 28:44.423
-He's gotta be here somewhere.
-l'm on it.

28:44.597 --> 28:48.260
My name is Oliver Queen,
and I am a coward.

28:49.394 --> 28:52.306
I'm a thief, and....

28:53.648 --> 28:55.479
And I am....

28:57.652 --> 28:58.983
TOYMAN:
Too ashamed to admit...

28:59.154 --> 29:02.646
...that you were really responsible
for killing Lex Luthor.

29:02.824 --> 29:05.315
You didn't think twice
about blaming me for it.

29:17.338 --> 29:21.456
We have to get these people out of here
now. Oliver's standing on a landmine.

29:21.634 --> 29:22.840
Just give me one second.

29:25.388 --> 29:27.253
OLIVER:
And |....

29:29.517 --> 29:30.848
Confess.

29:37.984 --> 29:39.099
[FIRE ALARM BLARING]

29:39.277 --> 29:41.609
MAN [OVER PA]:
The emergency alarm has been activated.

29:41.780 --> 29:46.274
Please move in an orderly fashion
to the nearest exit. Thank you.

29:46.451 --> 29:49.318
I'm not gonna ask. Nice one, Chloe.

29:53.208 --> 29:55.540
MAN [OVER PA]:
The emergency alarm has been activated.

29:55.710 --> 29:59.248
Please move in an orderly fashion
to the nearest exit. Thank you.

30:00.924 --> 30:03.131
Winslow, how do I disarm the bomb?

30:03.301 --> 30:07.260
I don't know who you are,
but you're interrupting my game.

30:07.430 --> 30:10.467
I can't go changing the rules
for someone who isn't playing.

30:10.642 --> 30:16.182
-This isn't a game. It's a man's life.
-No. It is a game.

30:16.356 --> 30:18.438
And Toyman makes the rules now.

30:19.067 --> 30:22.855
What you're doing is pointless.
Oliver would never let those people die.

30:23.488 --> 30:26.730
MAN [OVER PA]: Please move
in an orderly fashion to the nearest exit.

30:28.076 --> 30:31.409
But you already know that, don't you?
You don't allow for human error.

30:31.579 --> 30:33.740
You have to control who wins.

30:33.915 --> 30:36.577
That's why you put a timer
on the factory bomb.

30:37.752 --> 30:42.212
The pressure plate that Oliver's standing
on is fake, isn't it? It's on a timer.

30:42.382 --> 30:44.418
You follow my work.

30:45.176 --> 30:47.508
It's always nice to have a fan.

30:49.597 --> 30:51.758
How long does Oliver have?

30:53.226 --> 30:54.261
Not long enough.

31:16.749 --> 31:18.876
You know what,
I might be your biggest fan.

31:19.085 --> 31:20.950
I know that the real Winslow Schott...

31:21.129 --> 31:23.415
...would wanna live
and dance on Oliver‘s grave.

31:23.590 --> 31:29.961
TOYMAN:
Five, four, three, two, two, two...

31:30.138 --> 31:33.676
...two, two, two....

31:37.103 --> 31:39.685
No one wins a game if you both lose.

31:41.733 --> 31:43.064
[GRUNTS]

31:54.329 --> 31:56.490
How'd you know
the pressure plate wasn't real?

32:03.755 --> 32:04.995
I didn't.

32:09.677 --> 32:11.213
Oliver.

32:14.432 --> 32:17.595
I waited till the last person got out, Clark.

32:20.563 --> 32:23.145
I knew the explosion wouldn't kill you.

32:47.590 --> 32:51.629
Winslow-- Yes, the real Winslow.
--has been arrested.

32:51.803 --> 32:55.341
Chloe was able to follow the feed
from the earpiece.

32:56.599 --> 32:59.306
He's on the way to Stryker’s
as we speak.

33:04.440 --> 33:05.941
Speak your mind, Clark.

33:09.278 --> 33:12.190
I haven't been paying enough attention
to everything.

33:13.783 --> 33:16.445
There's been danger all around me
that I haven't seen.

33:18.037 --> 33:20.699
Warning signs that I haven't noticed.

33:23.376 --> 33:26.618
And people in need
that I've neglected.

33:28.047 --> 33:30.629
I didn't realize how bad things are.

33:35.680 --> 33:37.921
I haven't been here for you. I'm sorry.

33:38.099 --> 33:41.637
Well, with all due respect, Clark,
I'm not sure I'm worth your concern.

33:42.770 --> 33:44.931
You know, when l was reading
that speech in there...

33:45.106 --> 33:47.017
...when I decided to, uh....

33:49.027 --> 33:53.111
That speech wasn't just a laundry list
of all my sins. It was....

33:55.491 --> 33:56.992
It was a fact sheet.

33:58.661 --> 34:01.653
Ever tell you how old I was
when my parents died?

34:03.583 --> 34:04.618
Five.

34:05.418 --> 34:08.000
I never really knew them very well.

34:08.504 --> 34:12.747
Everything about my life
is not really mine.

34:13.968 --> 34:15.924
It's theirs.

34:18.806 --> 34:20.797
I didn't earn it.

34:22.560 --> 34:24.266
And it's all a lie.

34:27.231 --> 34:30.689
You of all people know
what it's like to wear a mask, right?

34:32.904 --> 34:34.519
That's all this is.

34:34.697 --> 34:37.109
The Queen name.

34:37.283 --> 34:39.399
Green Arrow.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.494
Masks.

34:44.624 --> 34:47.787
And I just realized
there's nothing underneath them.

34:49.462 --> 34:53.501
There is something behind those masks.
You're just afraid to face it.

34:56.928 --> 34:58.919
You're not running away
from who you are.

34:59.097 --> 35:01.713
You're running away
from who you think you're becoming.

35:03.017 --> 35:04.848
But you don't have to face it alone.

35:07.980 --> 35:11.347
Just because you've given up
on Oliver Queen doesn't mean I have.

35:15.446 --> 35:17.027
Thank you.

35:19.909 --> 35:21.900
[SIRENS WAILING]

35:22.620 --> 35:24.986
Sounds like they're playing your song.

35:27.500 --> 35:30.333
Go on, get the hell out of here.
Go be a hero. Go.

35:43.224 --> 35:44.555
[OLIVER YELLS]

35:53.818 --> 35:58.357
I want my lawyer!

35:58.865 --> 36:02.824
Hello? Hello?

36:03.619 --> 36:07.703
I want my lawyer!
I know you can hear me out there!

36:16.632 --> 36:18.463
Loud and clear, Mr. Schott.

36:18.634 --> 36:23.924
Oh, I know you.
You're Oliver Queen's business partner.

36:24.557 --> 36:27.890
Sorry about
trying to kill your boyfriend.

36:31.647 --> 36:33.603
You're not here for revenge, are you?

36:33.774 --> 36:35.435
[CHUCKLES]

36:41.949 --> 36:44.281
Something like that.

36:46.746 --> 36:50.705
Leave Oliver the hell alone.

36:50.875 --> 36:52.206
[SCREAMS]

36:55.171 --> 36:58.208
-Pretty please?
-Help! Someone!

36:58.382 --> 36:59.417
[GRUNTS]

36:59.592 --> 37:00.672
Help!

37:04.055 --> 37:06.296
The guard will be back here any minute.

37:06.474 --> 37:07.634
You're crazy.

37:07.808 --> 37:10.140
That guard is going
on administrative leave...

37:10.311 --> 37:12.927
...and he and l have a little agreement.

37:15.149 --> 37:17.014
See, you tried to escape.

37:17.193 --> 37:20.230
And he was only defending himself
when he shot you in the knee.

37:20.404 --> 37:23.396
No. No, please.

37:23.574 --> 37:25.485
They'll put me in solitary.

37:27.203 --> 37:28.693
No. No.

37:28.871 --> 37:30.953
Which is exactly where
you'll need to be...

37:31.123 --> 37:33.785
...to spend some quality time
with your new toy.

37:34.543 --> 37:35.794
What new toy?

37:57.358 --> 37:58.939
It's....

38:00.903 --> 38:02.939
It's beautiful.

38:03.447 --> 38:06.234
Yes, it is.

38:09.120 --> 38:14.660
It's a meteor-rock-powered heart,
and you're gonna tell me how it works.

38:54.707 --> 38:57.369
You missed all the excitement last night.

38:58.669 --> 39:02.207
If I remember correctly,
it wasn't my excitement to have missed.

39:02.381 --> 39:03.541
Was it?

39:04.216 --> 39:06.377
I was expecting
to read about the exploits...

39:06.552 --> 39:09.544
...of Metropolis' journalistic savior
this morning.

39:10.389 --> 39:14.052
Well, that's the thing. I think I may have
bitten off more than I can chew.

39:14.560 --> 39:16.175
Really?

39:17.229 --> 39:18.730
What's this?

39:20.107 --> 39:21.938
It's, uh....

39:23.736 --> 39:25.146
It's me asking for help.

39:28.699 --> 39:32.237
I didn't exactly ﬁnish my story last night,
and I missed the deadline.

39:35.206 --> 39:36.787
Okay.

39:40.252 --> 39:42.834
I guess I'm not ready to ﬂy solo just yet.

39:45.549 --> 39:47.881
The sky is a big place.

39:48.344 --> 39:49.584
Uh-huh.

39:51.722 --> 39:53.223
Wow.

40:05.319 --> 40:07.059
There.

40:08.489 --> 40:10.901
Looks like you've got
one too many names on there.

40:13.702 --> 40:17.160
I just thought you'd wanna have
some creative input.

40:19.583 --> 40:22.825
Lois, I am sorry for letting you down.

40:27.842 --> 40:29.753
Is this an olive branch?

40:29.927 --> 40:32.839
Because there better be a whole tree
somewhere in here.

40:33.931 --> 40:37.515
And maybe a new pair ofjeans too.

40:37.685 --> 40:41.473
You know, it's not every day
Lois Lane allows herself to be stood up.

40:41.647 --> 40:44.764
Well, then it's a good thing
it was only like a date.

40:46.152 --> 40:47.437
Huh.

40:48.904 --> 40:50.235
I don't know how someone...

40:50.406 --> 40:53.739
...would get a second date
after messing things up like that.

40:55.161 --> 40:58.619
Well, if people were to try that again...

40:59.540 --> 41:02.657
...they might wanna do it
on a slower news day.

41:03.794 --> 41:05.409
Hypothetically speaking.

41:06.213 --> 41:08.329
Well, those don't come along
very often.

41:08.507 --> 41:09.963
No.

41:13.345 --> 41:16.803
I'm sure people would make sure
they got it right the next time.

41:17.641 --> 41:20.303
Hypothetically speaking, of course.

41:24.940 --> 41:26.976
My thoughts exactly.

42:16.075 --> 42:18.066
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]
